erhead Pub/sub, Store/Query and Compute. <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/stars/esteve/rmw_zenoh.svg\" alt=\"esteve/rmw_zenoh\"></li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T11:56:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"gbdev/awesome-gbdev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software Development</h2><h4>Experimental/Proof of Concepts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/pokemium/gbdk-go\">gbdk-go</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/pokemium/gbdk-go\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":15,\"repo\":\"pokemium/gbdk-go\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A compiler translates Go programs to C code. The output C code is built into GB ROM by GBDK.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T11:17:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bwItFdPt-6M\">Vue 3 Composition Api Introduction - Full Tutorial</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T10:00:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CrY8CF1gysA\">Building Real-time Applications with Blazor and GraphQL</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-28%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 12, 2020 - Come see how Blazor and GraphQL combined will revolutionize how we build rich SPA applications with .NET. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #3.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GIupo55GTro\">Application State in Blazor Apps</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-30%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 12, 2020 - Carl shows you the benefits of keeping application data outside components and pages, how to do cross-component change notifications, and how to persist that AppState to localstorage. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #3.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ceGzm-pBhx4\">From Web Forms to Blazor - Introducing the Blazor Web Forms Components</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-29%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 12, 2020 - There are millions of ASP.NET Web Forms applications out there. How do you migrate them to .NET Core? With Blazor of course! In this talk, learn about the easy steps you can take to successfully migrate your application to Blazor with the BlazorWebFormComponents. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #3.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bNrym4PqhgM\">Components in Blazor</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-29%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 12, 2020 - Blazor is the blazing word in the Microsoft Tech stack at the moment because you can run C# on the client. In this session, I will talk about what Razor components are, talk about their lifecycle, event handling, and how to pass information between Blazor Components. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #3.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gnYIqYNW54I\">Trailblazor: Building Dynamic Applications with Blazor</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-31%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 12, 2020 - Underpinning Blazor's ability to create interactive web UIs using C# instead of JavaScript is a robust component model which offers exciting new opportunities for developers to create dynamic web applications. In this session we will explore a modular application framework for Blazor called Oqtane. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #3.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TH0661ai_Mg\">Getting Started With Blazor</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-31%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 12, 2020 - In this session, we will introduce the core concepts for Blazor development, both client and server side. Then we will dive in to a Blazor Web Assembly example and look at how we can build rich client side apps in C#. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #3.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CEjqhTGrqDY\">Modern Web Development with Blazor &#x26; .NET 5</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-29%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 10, 2020 - Blazor isn't just for new apps! Blazor in .NET 5 is integrated seamlessly with ASP.NET Core to enable modern full stack web development with .NET. In this session we'll show you how you can use Blazor and ASP.NET Core together to add rich client-side interactivity to both new and existing apps. You'll learn how to use Blazor components from your existing MVC views and Razor Pages, handle server-side prerendering, setup authentication &#x26; authorization, improve load time performance, and then deploy your app into production. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #1.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nag6u5TxjIA\">A talk for trailblazers: Blazor in .NET 5</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-30%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> November 10, 2020 - Wondering what's in store for Blazor in .NET 5? Wonder no more! This talk features the latest and greatest features to arrive in Blazor as part of .NET 5. From improved APIs for working with the browser to CSS isolation to a variety of performance improvements, you'll leave this presentation with rundown of everything you'll be able to do in the latest version of Blazor. <a href=\"https://www.dotnetconf.net/\">.NET Conf 2020</a>, Day #1.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T09:51:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Kazhnuz/awesome-gnome","categoryHTML":"<h2>Extensions</h2><h3>Applets</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://extensions.gnome.org/extension/517/caffeine/\">Caffeine</a> - Applet that let you deactivate the GNOME lock screen.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T08:24:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"protontypes/awesome-robotic-tooling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Simultaneous Localization and Mapping</h2><h3>Visual</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/gradslam/gradslam\">gradslam</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/gradslam/gradslam\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">894</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":894,\"repo\":\"gradslam/gradslam\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An open source differentiable dense SLAM library for PyTorch.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T06:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"tramcar/awesome-job-boards","categoryHTML":"<h2>Gaming</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.workwithindies.com\">Work With Indies</a> - A single place find all the cool jobs in indie games</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T03:18:24.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"johnjago/awesome-free-software","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Video</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mpv.io/\">MPV</a> - Customizable multimedia player with scripting support. (<a href=\"https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv/blob/master/LICENSE.GPL/\">GNU GPLv2</a>)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-25T02:37:28.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1606262400000,"to":1606348799999,"previousId":"2020-11-26","nextId":"2020-11-24","nextName":"Nov 24th, 2020","previousName":"Nov 26th, 2020"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","4035379035"]}